item.title: Nulls, Nulls and Nulls oh my!
item.dc:creator: @jensie jensie
item.description:
@jensie wrote:

A null means that the item ID was not recognized by your client. Some servers were configured for the users custom made client, which would probably have other Item-ID’s than Silabs client. So to fix this you can: 1) Use a custom client or 2) Configure your server for Silab client. Which would be downloading her output.txt and integrate that into your Items.cfg or whatever it’s called, haven’t touched a private server in a while.
